<glossary>
<definition id="fs-idm350257408"><term>Talent acquisition</term>
<meaning id="fs-idm381032608">The process of finding and acquiring skilled candidates for employment within a company; it generally refers to a long-term view of building talent pipelines, rather than short-term recruitment.</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-idm375006192"><term>War for talent</term>
<meaning id="fs-idm344548144">Coined by McKinsey &amp; Company in 1997, it refers to the increasing competition for recruiting and retaining talented employees.</meaning>
</definition>
</glossary>
